---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import StarfieldBackground from '../../components/StarfieldBackground.astro';
import NavBar from '../../components/NavBar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';

const links = [
  { href: '/home#about', label: 'About' },
  { href: '/home#members', label: 'Members' },
  { href: '/thinking', label: 'Thinking' }
];
---
<BaseLayout title="Why AstroCademiX exists" description="Starter thinking note.">
  <StarfieldBackground />
  <NavBar links={links} />
  <main class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 760px;">
      <div class="section-kicker">Manifesto</div>
      <h1 class="section-title">Why AstroCademiX exists</h1>
      <div class="glass floating-panel">
        <p class="section-copy" style="max-width:none; margin-top:0;">
          This is a starter page. Replace it with a short origin story for the club. Explain why you wanted a space that feels more alive than a standard laboratory page and more thoughtful than a casual social feed.
        </p>
        <p class="section-copy" style="max-width:none;">
          A good first post can explain what kinds of problems matter to you, what kinds of methods attract you, and how the club wants to connect curiosity with actual scientific work.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
